cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CYBER 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes a large dataset of social network posts and studies the reposting behaviors of users. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also likely as the paper examines the content of the posts and categorizes them based on social phenomena. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with analyzing and categorizing large amounts of textual data. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper involves natural language processing tasks such as text classification and sentiment analysis. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon issues related to online security and privacy in social network usage.
